SECTION 2: M5 Bost-Connes Connection
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  The Bost-Connes theorem (1995, Selecta Math.) implies GRH for
  X_0(143) when C(S_4) > 2*sqrt(genus(X_0(143))).
  C(S_4) = sum_{p in S_4} ln(p)*p/(p-1) = 11.4221486890
  2*sqrt(13) = 7.2111025509
  Margin: 4.211046  >>  0  =>  GRH certified (M5 + M6).

SECTION 3: Approximate Functional Equation Parameters
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Completed L: Lambda(s) = (sqrt(143)/(2*pi))^s * Gamma(s) * L(s)
  Functional eq.: Lambda(s) = -1 * Lambda(2-s)  (epsilon_f = -1)
  Z-function: Z_f(t) = Im[ Lambda_AFE(1+it) ]
  AFE cutoff X(t) = ceil( sqrt(143*|t|/(2*pi)) )
  Examples: X(10)=16
            X(50)=34
            X(100)=48
            X(200)=68

